  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency WaSH Support to Conflict-Affected Population</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Syrian Arab Republic is now ending its fifth year of civil crisis and a political solution remains elusive. Interventions is focused on maintaining existing water infrastructure and provide safe water through traditional life-saving WaSH assistance to affected population. The Action&apos;s aims mainly at supporting emergency maintenance /rehabilitation of water and sewage systems which has suffered greatly from the effects of the prolonged armed conflict and to increase the coping resources of affected population against continues water related emergencies. ACF is proposing an intervention for conflict affected and vulnerable individuals in Syria targeting both IDP and Host communities in Hassakeh, Aleppo, and Rural Damascus Governorates.
This proposed intervention aims at addressing several compounding factors which are imposing serious threats on the public health situation in the country and ensure access to safe clean water, sanitation services and hygiene promotion activities for 125,000 individuals. The intervention is elaborated to address needs through systems rehabilitation and emergency water supply activities such as water trucking, provision of fuel and distribution of related NFIs .  The intervention mainly aims at responding to the water cut in Aleppo city, water trucking needs for IDP communities in rural Damascus and the continues water problems in Hassakeh governorate through emergency WaSH activities.   ACF keeps flexibility regarding planned activities and target areas in order to be able to respond in a timely effective manner to affected population needs across the country including participation in convoys accessing besieged areas.</narrative>
  </description>
